title: Seut Baraing
text:
Seut Baraing ( born September 29, 1999 in <a href="Siem%20Reap%20Province">Siem Reap</a>, <a href="Cambodia">Cambodia</a>) is a Cambodian <a href="association%20footballer">football</a> player who currently plays for <a href="Phnom%20Penh%20Crown%20FC">Phnom Penh Crown</a> in the <a href="Cambodian%20League">Cambodian League</a>.
Club career.
Baraing joined Cambodian side Phnom Penh Crown in 2011 and progressed through their youth ranks. He made his debut in February 2016 against <a href="Cambodian%20Tiger%20FC">Cambodian Tiger</a>. He featured in both <a href="2017%20AFC%20Cup%20qualifying%20play-off%23Phnom%20Penh%20Crown%20v%20Home%20United">2017 AFC Cup qualifying play-off</a> games, as the "Crown" lost 7-3 over two legs to <a href="Singapore">Singapore</a>an side <a href="Home%20United%20FC">Home United</a>.
International career.
Baraing represented Cambodia's under 19 team at the <a href="2016%20AFF%20U-19%20Youth%20Championship">2016 AFF U-19 Youth Championship</a>, playing in three games. He was first called up to the senior side in January 2017 and made his full international debut in a 7-2 loss to <a href="Saudi%20Arabia%20national%20football%20team">Saudi Arabia</a>, in which he played 90 minutes. Having impressed in this game, despite the result, head coach <a href="Leonardo%20Vitorino">Leonardo Vitorino</a> claimed he was the best left-back in the country. He cemented his place in the team, and made his second appearance in a 3-2 loss to <a href="India%20national%20football%20team">India</a> later the same year.
